{
  "_comment": [
    "Pronunciation map for SPOKEN text only. Subtitles show the original — reading '512 MB' is",
    "clearer on screen than 'five hundred and twelve megabytes', and the whole point of the",
    "subtitle is to be scannable.",
    "",
    "Four sections, applied in this order:",
    "  units    - a number followed by a unit. Singular/plural chosen from the number.",
    "  symbols  - standalone characters that say either skips or mispronounces.",
    "  spell    - acronyms say attempts as words and gets wrong. Rendered letter by letter.",
    "  jargon   - shorthand expanded to full words.",
    "",
    "Case matters in units: MB is megabytes, Mb is megabits, and conflating them is a factor of",
    "eight. Everything else matches case-insensitively on whole words only, so 'repo' expands but",
    "'reporter' does not."
  ],

